{
  "texts": [
    "The middle row extracts one summary statistic for each curve in the top row and compares them across models.",
    "To test whether rhetorical citations benefit the three metrics of community health, one-tailed OLS regressions were performed without multiple comparisons.",
    "Data has been tested to ensure that they meet the assumptions of t-test.",
    "Panel d shows that, at the end of 1000 timesteps, quality, and citations are more correlated (+2.5%) in the full model than in either of the null models.",
    "Full-Null reference: t(39998) = 120.526, Cohen's d = 1.205, 95% CI = (0.019, 0.019), n = 20,000 (1000 steps × 20 runs); Full-Null threshold: t(39998) = 126.128, Cohen's d = 1.261, 95% CI = (0.019, 0.020), n = 20,000."
  ]
}